### FindMy Items API Tests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/items
@authToken = Bearer token

### 1. Get All Items
GET {{baseUrl}}

### 2. Get All Items (with filters)
GET {{baseUrl}}?type=lost&category=Phones&status=active

### 3. Search Items
GET {{baseUrl}}/search?q=phone

### 4. Get Single Item
# Replace ':id' with a valid item ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/:id

### 5. Post New Item
# Replace 'token' with a valid JWT from login
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Lost iPhone 15",
  "type": "lost",
  "category": "Phones",
  "description": "Black iPhone 15 Pro Max lost near Balme Library",
  "date": "2026-03-25",
  "location": "Balme Library",
  "locationDetails": "Near the entrance on the second floor",
  "rewardOffered": true
}

### 6. Edit Item
# Replace ':id' with the item ID and 'token' with a valid JWT
PUT {{baseUrl}}/:id
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Lost iPhone 15 Pro Max (Updated)",
  "description": "Black iPhone 15 Pro Max lost near Balme Library entrance",
  "status": "active"
}

### 7. Delete Item
# Replace ':id' with the item ID and 'token' with a valid JWT
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/:id
Authorization: {{authToken}}

### 8. Upload Item Images
# Replace ':id' with the item ID and 'token' with a valid JWT
# Use form-data with key 'images' and select image files
POST {{baseUrl}}/:id/images
Authorization: {{authToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="images"; filename="test.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test.jpg
--boundary--
